{{Quote|That was a really interesting exercise for me in terms of publicity casting and actually doing it and landing with absolutely zilch other than a credit for Star Wars and a letter from the casting director and George Lucas saying at the last moment they had decided to give him a computer-generated visage as well as voice. And it's amusing standing back and watching all that happen.|Marton Csokas, describing his experience in ''Attack of the Clones''|<ref name="NZHerald">{{WebCite|url=https://www.nzherald.co.nz/lifestyle/marton-csokas-swimming-with-hollywood-sharks/LEFFTUWT7F2G5DOAYLHGKTX3YQ/|text=Marton Csokas, swimming with Hollywood sharks|author=Baillie, Russell|work=[[Wikipedia:The New Zealand Herald|The New Zealand Herald]]|archivedate=20201113204338}}</ref>}}
'''Marton Csokas''' (born [[June 30]], [[1960s#1966|1966]], in [[Wikipedia:Invercargill|Invercargill]], [[Wikipedia:New Zealand|New Zealand]]) is a [[Wikipedia:New Zealander|New Zealander]] actor who was cast as [[Poggle the Lesser]] in the [[2002]] [[prequel trilogy]] film [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'']]. The character was ultimately rendered using visual effects and Csokas was uncredited for his performance. Csokas is also known for his role as [[W:c:lotr:Celeborn|Celeborn]] in [[Wikipedia:The Lord of the Rings (film series)|''The Lord of the Rings'' film series]].

==Biography==
{{Quote|It may sound a bit cliché, but you know immediately when someone's got the goods and I'm excited that he will be joining our cast.|Casting director Robin Gurland, on Csokas' casting in ''Attack of the Clones''|<ref name="Bio">{{SWArchive|url=episode-ii/bts/production/news20000718.html|text=Casting Update: Local Talent Continues}}</ref>}}
Marton Csokas was born in [[Wikipedia:Invercargill|Invercargill]], [[Wikipedia:New Zealand|New Zealand]] on [[June 30]], [[1960s#1966|1966]]. The [[Wikipedia:New Zealander|New Zealander]] actor rose to prominence as an actor through numerous film and television roles, including that of [[W:c:lotr:Celeborn|Celeborn]] in [[Wikipedia:The Lord of the Rings (film series)|''The Lord of the Rings'' film trilogy]], released between [[2001]] and [[2003]].<ref name="Encyclopedia" />

[[File:Poggle_Geo.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Csokas was cast as Poggle the Lesser (pictured) before George Lucas decided to create the character through CGI.]]
On [[July 18]], [[2000]], Csokas was announced to be joining the cast of the [[prequel trilogy]] film [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'']], with his role described as that of a [[planet]]ary leader. The announcement was accompanied with praise for Csokas' talents by casting director [[Robin Gurland]].<ref name="Bio" /> Csokas later described himself as feeling like a child by comparison to his ''[[Star Wars]]'' and ''Lord of the Rings'' co-star [[Christopher Lee]],<ref name="NZHerald" /> who was known for his iconic role as [[Wikipedia:Count Dracula|Count Dracula]] in the [[Wikipedia:Dracula (Hammer film series)|film series]] released by [[Wikipedia:Hammer Film Productions|Hammer Film Productions]] throughout the twentieth century.<ref name="Lee">{{InsiderCite|51|Christopher Lee: Rings of Fire}}</ref>

Towards the end of production, director [[George Lucas]] made the decision to render [[Poggle the Lesser]], Csokas's character, with visual effects and to use sound effects for his voice as well. Csokas received a letter from Gurland and Lucas about the change and described the process of his performance being removed aside from his credit as "amusing."<ref name="NZHerald" /> Poggle's role was also significantly reduced from what it was in the screenplay by the time production was running. [[Industrial Light & Magic]] animator [[Charles Alleneck]] was the model for animating Poggle's movements.<ref name="Behind the magic">{{InsiderCite|65|Behind the Magic}}</ref>

Sound designer [[Ben Burtt]] recorded himself reading Poggle's lines and played them backwards during rehearsals. Late in production,<ref name="Behind the magic" /> he recorded voice actor [[Ernie Fosselius]] reciting Poggle's lines in reverse. Fosseulius also recorded [[Wikipedia:Swahili language|Swahili]]-type clicking noises and the sound of him blowing on the edge of a piece of paper, which Burtt added to the character's voice.<ref name="Sounds">''[[The Sounds of Star Wars]]''</ref> Csokas was uncredited in the finished film,<ref name="AOTC">{{Film|II}}</ref> which premiered on [[May 16]], 2002.<ref name="Year">''[[Star Wars Year By Year: A Visual History, Updated and Expanded Edition]]''</ref> He was still described as the voice of Poggle in the reference book ''[[Mythmaking: Behind the Scenes of Attack of the Clones]]'',<ref name="Mythmaking">''[[Mythmaking: Behind the Scenes of Attack of the Clones]]''</ref> published in November 2002,<ref name="Myth date">{{SWArchive|url=episode-ii/release/publish/news20020419.html|text=First Look: ''Mythmaking''}}</ref> and in the [[Star Wars Insider 94|ninety-fourth issue]] of the ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine,<ref name="Fact">{{InsiderCite|94|The Empire Strikes Fact!}}</ref> which was first released at [[Celebration IV]], an event that commenced on [[May 24]], [[2007]].<ref name="Celebration date">{{SWArchive|url=community/event/celebration/news20060526.html|text=''Star Wars'' Celebration IV in Los Angeles To Mark 30th Anniversary of Saga}}</ref>

